/*
:name: mod_three
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: mod_three.foo
:pyrope_top: mod_three.foo
*/

// `a % 3` lowered to a base-4 digit-sum reduction (tolg lower_mod3): since
// 4 ≡ 1 (mod 3), `a ≡ Σ(base-4 digits of a) (mod 3)`. Each round sums the 2-bit
// groups with an adder tree until the value is in [0,3], then maps 3 → 0. No
// divider/`mod` cell is produced — only get_mask (shift), `+`, `==`. Covers a
// narrow (u4) and a wide (u16) dividend so the multi-round reduction is
// exercised. lgcheck proves it bit-exact against native Verilog `%`.
comb foo(a:u4, w:u16) -> (r4:u2, r16:u2) {
  r4  = a % 3
  r16 = w % 3
}
